JavaScript Documentation Website
Welcome to the JavaScript Documentation Website project! This repository contains the source code for a fully responsive documentation website focused on JavaScript. The website is built using HTML and CSS, showcasing a comprehensive guide to JavaScript programming.

Introduction
The JavaScript Documentation Website aims to provide a thorough and user-friendly guide to JavaScript. Whether you are a beginner or an experienced developer, this site serves as a valuable resource for learning and referencing JavaScript concepts, functions, and best practices.

Features
Comprehensive Documentation: Detailed sections covering JavaScript basics, advanced topics, and best practices.
Fully Responsive Design: Optimized for desktop, tablet, and mobile devices.
Clean and Modern Layout: Easy-to-navigate structure with a focus on readability.
Interactive Code Snippets: Embedded code examples that enhance learning.
Search Functionality: Quickly find topics and keywords within the documentation.

Technologies Used
HTML: The backbone of the website's structure.
CSS: For styling and ensuring a responsive, visually appealing design.
JavaScript: Included in examples and interactive elements.

